-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530784\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 30, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104oxa1665702908679.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/oxa1665702908679.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/oxa1665702908679.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"oxa1665702908679\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Browser Security\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Web browsers are the clients in a web application, responsible for sending and receiving data to and from the server. The browser interprets and displays HTML, and makes use of interpreters for programming scripts such as JavaScript, PHP, and Flash. It is therefore vulnerable to attacks that intercept and read the data it sends, or cross-site scripting attacks such as site forgery.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"oxa1665702908679__section_w5253ab1b5b1_w5254ab1b5_w5255ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d933378e51\">\n                        \n Threats\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"oxa1665702908679__li_d20789e1_d20790e1_d20791e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ajn1665702669971.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ajn1665702669971.html\" title=\"Eavesdropping is a web security threat in which intermediate servers or sniffer programs intercept and read HTTP data packets as they traverse intermediate servers en route to their destination.\">Eavesdropping</a>—monitoring and logging the data exchange between the client and server by an intermediate server or sniffing software.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"oxa1665702908679__li_d20792e1_d20793e1_d20794e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ipn1665702669895.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ipn1665702669895.html\" title=\"Cross-site request forgery (also known as CSRF or XSRF), is a type of the web site attack in which a malicious script or URL sends an HTTP request to an external site for which the user is currently authenticated.\">Cross-Site Request Forgery</a>—a malicious script or URL sends an HTTP request to an external site for which the user is currently authenticated.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"oxa1665702908679__li_d20795e1_d20796e1_d20797e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pxc1665702669673.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pxc1665702669673.html\" title=\"Data leaks can result from incorrectly specified cookies, unverified client input, and verbose error messages.\">Data Leaks</a>—data leaks can provide information that is subsequently used for malicious purposes.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530784\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530784\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Browser Security Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 30, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Browser Security Web browsers are the clients in a web application, responsible for sending and receiving data to and from the server. The browser interprets and displays HTML, and makes use of interpreters for programming scripts such as JavaScript, PHP, and Flash. It is therefore vulnerable to attacks that intercept and read the data it sends, or cross-site scripting attacks such as site forgery. Threats Eavesdropping —monitoring and logging the data exchange between the client and server by an intermediate server or sniffing software. Cross-Site Request Forgery —a malicious script or URL sends an HTTP request to an external site for which the user is currently authenticated. Data Leaks —data leaks can provide information that is subsequently used for malicious purposes. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}